pokedex_entries = {"Abra":"Using its ability to read minds, it will identify impending danger and TELEPORT to safety.","Aerodactyl":"A ferocious, pre- historic Pokémon that goes for the enemy's throat with its serrated saw-like fangs.","Alakazam":"Its brain can out- perform a super- computer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5,000.","Arbok":"It is rumored that the ferocious warning markings on its belly differ from area to area.","Arcanine":"A Pokémon that has been admired since the past for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.","Articuno":"A legendary bird Pokémon that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.","Beedrill":"Flies at high speed and attacks using its large venomous stingers on its forelegs and tail.","Bellsprout":"A carnivorous Pokémon that traps and eats bugs. It uses its root feet to soak up needed moisture.","Blastoise":"A brutal Pokémon with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high speed tackles.","Bulbasaur":"A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this Pokémon.","Butterfree":"In battle, it flaps its wings at high speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.","Caterpie":"Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.","Chansey":"A rare and elusive Pokémon that is said to bring happiness to those who manage to get it.","Charizard":"Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to cause forest fires unintentionally.","Charmander":"Obviously prefers hot places. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.","Charmeleon":"When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the temperature to unbearably high levels.","Clefable":"A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.","Clefairy":"Its magical and cute appeal has many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.","Cloyster":"When attacked, it launches its horns in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.","Cubone":"Because it never removes its skull helmet, no one has ever seen this Pokémon's real face.","Dewgong":"Stores thermal energy in its body. Swims at a steady 8 knots even in intensely cold waters.","Diglett":"Lives about one yard underground where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears above ground.","Ditto":"Capable of copying an enemy's genetic code to instantly transform itself into a duplicate of the enemy.","Dodrio":"Uses its three brains to execute complex plans. While two heads sleep, one head stays awake.","Doduo":"A bird that makes up for its poor flying with its fast foot speed. Leaves giant footprints.","Dragonair":"A mystical Pokémon that exudes a gentle aura. Has the ability to change climate conditions.","Dragonite":"An extremely rarely seen marine Pokémon. Its intelligence is said to match that of humans.","Dratini":"Long considered a mythical Pokémon until recently when a small colony was found living underwater.","Drowzee":"Puts enemies to sleep then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating bad dreams.","Dugtrio":"A team of DIGLETT triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.","Eevee":"Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element STONEs.","Ekans":"Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole.","Electabuzz":"Normally found near power plants, they can wander away and cause major blackouts in cities.","Electrode":"It stores electric energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation.","Exeggcute":"Often mistaken for eggs. When disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.","Exeggutor":"Legend has it that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an EXEGGCUTE.","Farfetch'd":"The sprig of green onions it holds is its weapon. It is used much like a metal sword.","Fearow":"With its huge and magnificent wings, it can keep aloft without ever having to land for rest.","Flareon":"When storing thermal energy in its body, its temperature could soar to over 1600 degrees.","Gastly":"Almost invisible, this gaseous Pokémon cloaks the target and puts it to sleep without notice.","Gengar":"Under a full moon, this Pokémon likes to mimic the shadows of people and laugh at their fright.","Geodude":"Found in fields and mountains. Mistaking them for boulders, people often step or trip on them.","Gloom":"The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn't drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.","Golbat":"Once it strikes, it will not stop draining energy from the victim even if it gets too heavy to fly.","Goldeen":"Its tail fin billows like an elegant ballroom dress, giving it the nickname of the Water Queen.","Golduck":"Often seen swim- ming elegantly by lake shores. It is often mistaken for the Japanese monster, Kappa.","Golem":"Its boulder-like body is extremely hard. It can easily withstand dynamite blasts without damage.","Graveler":"Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction.","Grimer":"Appears in filthy areas. Thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.","Growlithe":"Very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.","Gyarados":"Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.","Haunter":"Because of its ability to slip through block walls, it is said to be from an- other dimension.","Hitmonchan":"While apparently doing nothing, it fires punches in lightning fast volleys that are impossible to see.","Hitmonlee":"When in a hurry, its legs lengthen progressively. It runs smoothly with extra long, loping strides.","Horsea":"Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.","Hypno":"When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of PSI moves such as HYPNOSIS and CONFUSION.","Ivysaur":"When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.","Jigglypuff":"When its huge eyes light up, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.","Jolteon":"It accumulates negative ions in the atmosphere to blast out 10000- volt lightning bolts.","Jynx":"It seductively wiggles its hips as it walks. It can cause people to dance in unison with it.","Kabuto":"A Pokémon that was resurrected from a fossil found in what was once the ocean floor eons ago.","Kabutops":"Its sleek shape is perfect for swim- ming. It slashes prey with its claws and drains the body fluids.","Kadabra":"It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being close by.","Kakuna":"Almost incapable of moving, this Pokémon can only harden its shell to protect itself from predators.","Kangaskhan":"The infant rarely ventures out of its mother's protective pouch until it is 3 years old.","Kingler":"The large pincer has 10000 hp of crushing power. However, its huge size makes it unwieldy to use.","Koffing":"Because it stores several kinds of toxic gases in its body, it is prone to exploding without warning.","Krabby":"Its pincers are not only powerful weapons, they are used for balance when walking sideways.","Lapras":"A Pokémon that has been over- hunted almost to extinction. It can ferry people across the water.","Lickitung":"Its tongue can be extended like a chameleon's. It leaves a tingling sensation when it licks enemies.","Machamp":"Using its heavy muscles, it throws powerful punches that can send the victim clear over the horizon.","Machoke":"Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power save belt to be able to regulate its motions.","Machop":"Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger.","Magikarp":"In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.","Magmar":"Its body always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly among flames.","Magnemite":"Uses anti-gravity to stay suspended. Appears without warning and uses THUNDER WAVE and similar moves.","Magneton":"Formed by several MAGNEMITEs linked together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.","Mankey":"Extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment then thrashing away the next instant.","Marowak":"The bone it holds is its key weapon. It throws the bone skillfully like a boomerang to KO targets.","Meowth":"Adores circular objects. Wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.","Metapod":"This Pokémon is vulnerable to attack while its shell is soft, exposing its weak and tender body.","Mew":"So rare that it is still said to be a mirage by many experts. Only a few people have seen it worldwide.","Mewtwo":"It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene splicing and DNA engineering experiments.","Moltres":"Known as the legendary bird of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flash of flames.","Mr.Mime":"If interrupted while it is miming, it will slap around the offender with its broad hands.","Muk":"Thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.","Nidoking":"It uses its powerful tail in battle to smash, constrict, then break the prey's bones.","Nidoqueen":"Its hard scales provide strong protection. It uses its hefty bulk to execute powerful moves.","Nidoran♀":"Although small, its venomous barbs render this Pokémon dangerous. The female has smaller horns.","Nidoran♂":"Stiffens its ears to sense danger. The larger its horns, the more powerful its secreted venom.","Nidorina":"The female's horn develops slowly. Prefers physical attacks such as clawing and biting.","Nidorino":"An aggressive Pokémon that is quick to attack. The horn on its head secretes a powerful venom.","Ninetales":"Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1000-year curse.","Oddish":"During the day, it keeps its face buried in the ground. At night, it wanders around sowing its seeds.","Omanyte":"Although long extinct, in rare cases, it can be genetically resurrected from fossils.","Omastar":"A prehistoric Pokémon that died out when its heavy shell made it impossible to catch prey.","Onix":"As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to a diamond, but colored black.","Paras":"Burrows to suck tree roots. The mushrooms on its back grow by draw- ing nutrients from the bug host.","Parasect":"A host-parasite pair in which the parasite mushroom has taken over the host bug. Prefers damp places.","Persian":"Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.","Pidgeot":"When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as MAGIKARP.","Pidgeotto":"Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this Pokémon will fiercely peck at any intruder.","Pidgey":"A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.","Pikachu":"When several of these Pokémon gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.","Pinsir":"If it fails to crush the victim in its pincers, it will swing it around and toss it hard.","Poliwag":"Its newly grown legs prevent it from running. It appears to prefer swimming than trying to stand.","Poliwhirl":"Capable of living in or out of water. When out of water, it sweats to keep its body slimy.","Poliwrath":"An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breast stroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.","Ponyta":"Its hooves are 10 times harder than diamonds. It can trample anything completely flat in little time.","Porygon":"A Pokémon that consists entirely of programming code. Capable of moving freely in cyberspace.","Primeape":"Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until it is caught.","Psyduck":"While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily Pokémon will use psychokinetic powers.","Raichu":"Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high voltage power.","Rapidash":"Very competitive, this Pokémon will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.","Raticate":"It uses its whis- kers to maintain its balance. It apparently slows down if they are cut off.","Rattata":"Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.","Rhydon":"Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees.","Rhyhorn":"Its massive bones are 1000 times harder than human bones. It can easily knock a trailer flying.","Sandshrew":"Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for food.","Sandslash":"Curls up into a spiny ball when threatened. It can roll while curled up to attack or escape.","Scyther":"With ninja-like agility and speed, it can create the illusion that there is more than one.","Seadra":"Capable of swim- ming backwards by rapidly flapping its wing-like pectoral fins and stout tail.","Seaking":"In the autumn spawning season, they can be seen swimming power- fully up rivers and creeks.","Seel":"The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick ice.","Shellder":"Its hard shell repels any kind of attack. It is vulnerable only when its shell is open.","Slowbro":"The SHELLDER that is latched onto SLOWPOKE's tail is said to feed on the host's left over scraps.","Slowpoke":"Incredibly slow and dopey. It takes 5 seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.","Snorlax":"Very lazy. Just eats and sleeps. As its rotund bulk builds, it becomes steadily more slothful.","Spearow":"Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speed to stay airborne.","Squirtle":"After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.","Starmie":"Its central core glows with the seven colors of the rainbow. Some people value the core as a gem.","Staryu":"An enigmatic Pokémon that can effortlessly regenerate any appendage it loses in battle.","Tangela":"The whole body is swathed with wide vines that are similar to sea- weed. Its vines shake as it walks.","Tauros":"When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.","Tentacool":"Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by its stinging acid.","Tentacruel":"The tentacles are normally kept short. On hunts, they are extended to ensnare and immobilize prey.","Vaporeon":"Lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin which is often mistaken for a mermaid's.","Venomoth":"The dust-like scales covering its wings are color coded to indicate the kinds of poison it has.","Venonat":"Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats insects. It is attracted by light at night.","Venusaur":"The plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.","Victreebel":"Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.","Vileplume":"The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.","Voltorb":"Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Pokéball, they have zapped many people.","Vulpix":"At the time of birth, it has just one tail. The tail splits from its tip as it grows older.","Wartortle":"Often hides in water to stalk unwary prey. For swimming fast, it moves its ears to maintain balance.","Weedle":"Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp venomous stinger on its head.","Weepinbell":"It spits out POISONPOWDER to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of ACID.","Weezing":"Where two kinds of poison gases meet, 2 KOFFINGs can fuse into a WEEZING over many years.","Wigglytuff":"The body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.","Zapdos":"A legendary bird Pokémon that is said to appear from clouds while dropping enormous lightning bolts.","Zubat":"Forms colonies in perpetually dark places. Uses ultrasonic waves to identify and approach targets."}